His voice has been described as "spellbinding" and "elegiac" by The New York Times.

As a recording artist, he strives to make emotionally intelligent music that spans a variety of genres and approaches. Drawing on his extensive training in classical and improvised music as well as a variety of experiences in the performance art and experimental theater worlds, he aims to express truths relevant to the inner lives of people living in current times while maintaining a sense of timelessness.

He has performed with and co-written projects for BalletX, Pennsylvania Shakespeare Festival, Leah Stein Dance Company and Pauline Oliveros. He has presented durational performance pieces at art festivals and improvised silent film scores at The International House of Philadelphia for the UCLA festival of Preservation. Mars has performed at Carnegie Hall, The Joyce Theater, The Vilar Center, The Philadelphia Museum of Art and The Trocadero to name a few.
